Sacyr Shareholders Want to Sell 10% of Repsol, Economista Says

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-10-19T06:33:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/sacyr-shareholders-want-to-sell-10-of-repsol-economista-says.html
Sacyr Vallehermoso SA (SYV) ’s shareholders
Demetrio Carceller, Juan Abello and a group of Spanish banks
will propose the sale of a 10 percent stake in  Repsol YPF SA (REP)  to
repay debt at a board meeting tomorrow,  El Economista  reported.  The shareholders, who jointly control 9 percent of Sacyr,
want proceeds of the sale to be used to cut the company’s debt
of around 5 billion euros ($6.9 billion), the newspaper said,
citing unidentified people with knowledge of the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
